  <td>
   
   <font class="ArticleSource"><big>Reader Editorial:</big></font>
   <font class="ArticleHead"><big>New Server Transfers and EQ Legends</big></font>
   <font class="ArticleAuthorLight">&nbsp;filed by </font><font class="ArticleAuthor">Vopi Ululant</font>
   <div align="right">
   <font class="ArticleTime">03/11/2003 01:38 PM CST &nbsp;&nbsp; 11 Comments</font>
   <div align="left">
   <font class="ArticleText"><I>Editor's Note: This is a reader-submitted piece and therefore doesn't represent the opinions of the Mobhunter staff. But since we don't personally play on the Stormhammer server and have been getting a few letters of this type lately, it seemed a good time to present this player's viewpoint.</I><p>As a long time EverQuest player, I grew tired of the political environment of my server following the release of the Plains of Power expansion, and decided to transfer over Stormhammer.  Subscribing to the EverQuest Legends service was the only way to move to another server without losing equipment; the extra features advertised on the SOE web site were merely iceing on the cake.<p>It didn't take me long to realize that those bonus features, for all intent, don't actually exist.  The Legends web site (character pages, guild pages, etc.) is severely broken, and has been for a long time.  Customer service coverage is not 24 x 7, and hasn't been since at least the customer service reorganization which reduced service levels across all of the servers.  There currently is no Legends specific in game content, and hasn't been since the Sleeper's Tomb/Skyshrine revamps went to the normal servers.<p>What does that leave?  Of the advertised features, only one still exists: GM events.  Unfortunately, GM events no longer have a consistent story to them, and no longer introduce anything actually unique into the game (&quot;Supreme Advernturer&quot; items and such are merely the equivalent of door prizes).  That one remaining advertised feature is just a shell of what it was meant to be, and just a shell of what it is still protrayed to be in the advertising materials.<p>You may ask why people stay on Stormhammer, then.  Most of the long term Stormhammer players are refugees from the PvP servers, and have no where else to go.  The rest have found the generally more mature, and smaller, player base on the server to be more desireable than returning to their original server, even if it means saving a bit of money.<p>Now we have a new server, one to which Sony will happily move you, complete with items, for a fee.  They are essentially selling, for the regular monthly price, the same thing that Legends customers are getting for vastly more money.  Of course, they realize this, because they expressly forbid transfers from Legends to the new server.  Every other customer can transfer characters to the new server, except for Legends customers.<p>The manner in which the Legends service is sold has a name in the real world.  It's called bait and switch, and is usually frowned upon. And now the one thing that really was specific to the service isn't.<p>It's time for Sony to simply throw in the towel for the Legends service, and turn Stormhammer into a regular blue server.  They've mismanaged the service into a failure, and it's time to stop ripping off the customers which they misled into subscribing to it.<br></font>
  </td>
 </tr>
</table>
